items.details: Healthy recipes begin with Wild Veggie. USDA organic. Non-GMO project verified. Kosher certified. Soups. Smoothies. Sauces. For more easy recipes visit 101 ways to Wild Veggie at www.wildveggie.com. We make eating your veggies quick, easy & deliciously healthy! Quick-cooked and flash-frozen, Wild Veggie puree captures the incredible, pure flavor and amazing nutrients of organically grown, fresh, vegetables - and since Wild Veggie is frozen, it's easy to always have fresh veggies on hand. Wild Veggie makes it easy to create vegetable rich soups, sauces, dips and smoothies without all the prep and mess! Vegan. Lower sodium. Gluten free. Low in calories. Kosher certified. Certified organic by QAI.
items.directions: Simply defrost and mix-in Wild Veggie to quickly make your favorite foods. Soup! Heat & spice for a simple soup or add more goodies for a complete soup. Sauce! Defrost & pour over pasta or into recipe to veggie-up your meal. Dip! Add tofu or cream, spices and herbs for incredibly delicious fresh tasting dips. Smoothie! Mix with ice, fruit juice and yogurt for a fresh Wild Veggie smoothie.
items.ingredients: Organic Butternut Squash, Water, Organic Potato Starch, Contains Less than 2% of the Following: Organic Safflower Oil, Sea Salt, Organic Vegetables (Carrot, Tomato, Onion, Potato, Garlic), Organic Dextrose, Organic Evaporated Cane Syrup, Organic Canola Oil, Organic Spices.

items.directions: Keep frozen. Stove Top: 1. Bring 1/2 cup water to a boil. 2. Add chopped kale and 1/2 teaspoon salt, if desired. 3. Bring rapidly to a second boil separating with fork to hasten thawing. 4. Cover and reduce heat. Simmer 10-12 minutes (For food safety and best quality, cook to a temperature of 160 degrees F. Cooking times may vary depending on power of microwave and type of container used. To retain highest quality and texture, do not overcook). 5. Drain and serve with butter and seasonings to taste. Microwave: Place kale and 2 tablespoons water in a microwave-safe casserole. Cover. 2. Cook on high for 5-6 minutes (For food safety and best quality, cook to a temperature of 160 degrees F. Cooking times may vary depending on power of microwave and type of container used. To retain highest quality and texture, do not overcook). Stir. 3. Cook on high for another 2-3 minutes or until tender. Drain. Keep frozen until ready to use.
